AB  - This paper considers properties of a generalized version of the traditional two-sector, two-factor model underlying, for example, the Heckscher-Ohlin theory. Versions of the model have recently been employed to study intra-industry trade. One sector is of the traditional type, whereas in the other sector firms exhibit internal increasing returns to scale, products are differentiated, and Chamberlinian monopolistic competition prevails. The main focus is on how non-homotheticity in this sector's technology affects the dual equilibrium relationships between factor and commodity relative prices, and between relative factor endowments and relative industry outputs.
