UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199683900247
AB  - Recent porfolio balance models of exchange rate determination under rational expectations are extended to determine jointly the exchange rates, spot and forward, the interest rate, and the current account. With risk aversion, domestic and foreign bonds are not perfect substitutes, despite capital mobility, so that the difference between domestic and foreign interest rates is not equal to the expected rate of depreciation or, equivalently, the forward rate is a biased predictor of the spot rate. The forecast bias is studied following current account and money supply disturbances, distinguishing among permanent or temporary, and anticipated or unanticipated changes.
