AB  - This paper develops three models for the determination of foreign exchange futures prices under fixed exchange rates and expectations of devaluation. These models show that certain characteristics of futures prices behavior that have been used as proof of inefficiency may be present even if the market is efficient. They also have several implications that are consistent with the observed behavior of Mexican Pesos futures prices.
